By Chibuike
Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata
Post) – President Muhammadu Buhari on Friday met separately with three
ministers at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. He met with the
Minister of Aviation, Hadi Sirika; Minister of Niger Delta, Godswill Akpabio
and the Minister of Science and Technology, Ogbonanya Onu. The first
meeting was with Sirika around 11.30am, followed by Akpabio at 12pm, and Onu
around 12.30pm. The meetings are coming ahead of President Buhari’s scheduled visit to Bokina Faso with some governors tomorrow for ECOWAS Head of Government meeting on counter-terrorism.